<HEAD>Air Force Planes Collide In The Air, 2 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two air force planes collided in the air
in eastern India, killing one pilot and spewing fiery debris that
killed a youth on the ground and injured four civilians, Press Trust
of India reported.
   The report said Friday's crash seriously injured the second
pilot. It did not specify where the accident occurred.
   The falling wreckage killed a teen-ager and burned four people on
the ground, the report said. It said fire from the debris burned
three houses.
   An air force official contacted in New Delhi said he had no
information on the collision. The news agency said the pilots were
on a training mission.
