<1ST_LINE>r i PM-India-Nudity     12-03 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-India-Nudity,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Goa Bans Nudity On Beaches</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Public nudity has been banned in Goa,
whose white sandy beaches have long attracted tourists searching for
the allover suntan, Press Trust of India said today.
   Plainclothes policemen have been posted on the beaches of the
former Portuguese enclave, and patrol boats will keep watch to
enforce the ban, PTI said.
   ``Nudism is not allowed and violators are liable to punishment,''
say billboards set up at all major beaches in the west coast resort.
PTI did not say what the punishment would be.
   Tens of thousands of foreign and Indian tourists visit Goa every
year.
   The ban was imposed because Indians, who usually travel in
families, said they were embarrassed by the public display of
nudity, PTI said.
   Goans who operate tourist resorts also complained that nude
sunbathing was a bad influence on their children, the news agency
said.
</TEXT>
