<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     12-03 0407</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0419</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Big Chill In Deep South</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Brisk weather chilled the South today as a high-pressure system
expanded from Texas into America's southeast quarter, generating
light winds and making the mercury plummet.
   Temperatures early this morning were in the 20s and 30s from
Mississippi to northern Florida.
   Freeze warnings were in effect through southern Alabama, northern
Florida and the Carolinas' coast.
   The only notable precipitation across the nation was in northern
Vermont, where widely scattered snow fell.
   Skies were mostly clear across much of the nation, but cloudy
skies covered central California and clouds and dense fog were
reported in much of the Pacific Northwest.
   Today's forecast called for showers over much of Michigan, with
rain turning to snow over the Upper Michigan; widely scattered snow
in northwest Montana; and gusty winds through the central Plains and
upper Mississippi Valley.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 30s in the northern
Rockies, from northeast Montana to North Dakota, the upper
Mississippi Valley and northern sections of the upper Great Lakes
and in northern Maine; the 60s from the central California coast to
central Arizona, southern New Mexico, western Texas, Oklahoma, much
of the lower Mississippi Valley, the Tennessee Valley, southern
sections of the lower Ohio Valley and from the central Gulf Coast to
northern Florida and the middle and southern Atlantic coast; the 70s
in Southern California and parts of the desert Southwest, central
and eastern Texas and southern Florida; and in the 40s and 50s in
the rest of the country.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 11
degrees at Craig, Colo., to 64 degrees at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 32 fair; Boston 39 cloudy; Buffalo 37 windy;
Charleston, S.C. 35 fair; Cincinnati 34 fair; Cleveland 34 fair;
Detroit 34 fair; Miami 60 cloudy; New York 38 fair; Philadelphia 34
fair; Pittsburgh 31 fair; Portland, Maine 35 cloudy; Washington 37
fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 37 fair; Chicago 41 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 46
fair; Denver 26 fair; Des Moines 39 fair; Indianapolis 37 fair;
Kansas City 44 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 30 fair; Nashville 29
fair; New Orleans 38 fair; St. Louis 47 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 29 fair; Anchorage 19 snow; Las Vegas 42 fair;
Los Angeles 60 partly cloudy; Phoenix 53 fair; Salt Lake City 24
foggy; San Diego 54 fair; San Francisco 52 cloudy; Seattle 40 foggy.
   _Canada: Montreal 36 partly cloudy; Toronto 32 fair.
</TEXT>
