<1ST_LINE>r w PM-Bush-Hanukkah 1stLd-Writethru a0805 12-03 0168</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Bush-Hanukkah, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0805,220</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 1st graf to CORRECT beginning of Hanukkah to tonight;
picks up 2nd graf pvs, bgng: ``On Saturday...''</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a message from President-elect George
Bush on the Jewish holiday of Hanukkah, which begins tonight, as
released by the office of the vice president:
   On Saturday night, Jewish Americans will light the first of eight
candles as the eight-day Jewish holiday, Hanukkah, the Festival of
Lights, begins.
   Barbara and I extend to everyone celebrating Hannukah our best
wishes for a happy holiday as we recall the words of the prophet
Zechariah, ``Not by might, nor by power, but by My Spirit saith the
Lord of hosts.''
   The triumph of religious liberty shines like a beacon for the
world to see. Our forefathers, guided by that same light, struggled
to come to this land in a similar pursuit of the freedom to worship.
Upon our faith in the Lord rests the great strength of the United
States of America.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
