<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Nuclear Shutdown,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Nuclear Power Plant Shuts Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yugoslavia's only nuclear power plant
has shut down because of a defect in a recently installed
transformer, the state news agency Tanjug reported Saturday.
   It said the damage at the Krsko plant in Slovenia was caused by a
short circuit between the electric equipment and the ground
connection causing a sudden drop in the power output and the
shutdown of the plant.
   The generator and the 21-kilowatt transformer were shut down
Friday night and preparations for repair were under way, Tanjug said.
   It said the transformer was installed Wednesday to replace one
damaged in a storm.
   The 632-kilowatt station has been in operation since the 1970s.
