<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Window Death,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Suffocates While Stuck In Father's Bedroom Window</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GATES, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man trying to climb through a window at his
father's home got stuck in a 9-inch opening and suffocated, police
said.
   Police said Rocky Benedetto's body was found Thursday night by
his father, Angelo, at the elder Benedetto's home in this Rochester
suburb. The son's body was stuck at the chest in a ground-floor
bedroom window, his head inside and feet dangling 18 inches above
the ground outside, police said.
   A autopsy report by the Monroe County medical examiner's office
said Benedetto, 31, of Pittsford, died of asphyxia due to
compression to his chest. His death was ruled an accident.
   ``He got stuck in there and by violently trying to get out he did
more damage than help,'' said Police Chief Thomas Roche.
   The elder Benedetto said he didn't know why his son didn't use
his key.
</TEXT>
