<1ST_LINE>u a AM-NYLottery 1stLd-Writethru a0547 12-03 0394</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-NY Lottery, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0547,0401</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>$45 Million Jackpot Triggers Ticket Frenzy</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS with 3 grafs to UPDATE with winning number. Picks up 4th
graf pvs, `If a...'.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By KILEY ARMSTRONG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Would-be millionaires snapped up lottery tickets
at a rate of 28,000 a minute Saturday, lining up for a chance for at
least $45 million, New York's biggest-ever jackpot.
   There was no immediate word on whether anyone had chosen the
winning combination chosen late Saturday, which was heavy on the
number 8: 1-8-13-18-28-48. Lottery officials said it would probably
take until sometime Sunday for computers to calculate the final
jackpot and determine whether anyone got it.
   ``I actually wouldn't know what to do with that kind of money.
But I bet I'd suddenly find a lot of friends to help me spend it,''
said Noreen O'Brien of Cliffside Park, N.J.
   If a single ticketholder won the $45 million Lotto jackpot, he
would get about $1.7 million a year for 20 years after withholding
taxes. The odds of winning the biggest jackpot in the 12-year-old
state lottery were 12.9 million to 1.
   For a $1 ticket, a player chooses two combinations of six numbers
from 1 to 54.
   Lines stretched outside stationery, tobacco and drug stores
throughout the state in temperatures mostly in the upper 40s.
   The pace started picking up Friday evening, when sales increased
from 18,000 a minute to 22,000 at the 5,800 computerized ticket
outlets statewide.
   By Saturday morning, they reached 28,000 tickets a minute, said
Bill Knowlton, a spokesman for the lottery.
   The jackpot rose to a guaranteed $45 million after no one picked
the winning numbers in Wednesday's drawing, when the jackpot was $26
million.
   Acting Lottery Director Russell Gladieux said Friday the jackpot
could go slightly higher, depending on sales.
   The world's biggest lottery jackpot, $61.98 million, was divided
among three tickets in California in October; one ticket was held by
25 co-workers and another was held by 15.
   The largest single winner was a Florida woman who claimed $55.16
million in September.
   The largest previous jackpot in New York was $41 million in 1985.
That was divided among three winning tickets, including one held by
21 factory workers.
   The biggest single winner in New York state lottery history was a
man who won $30.5 million in 1986.
</TEXT>
